HEADWORD: Doggedness
<hw>Dog"ged*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sullenness;
moroseness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sullen or obstinate determination; grim resolution
or persistence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dogger</ent>⟦br⟧
